---
Source:
  - Title: Treasury of Traditional Wisdom
    Page: 30
By: Mechthiljd of Magdeburg
Tags:
  - Creation=Inexhaustibility of the Creator
  - Creation=Self-Revelation
---
As God willed no longer to remain in Himself, alone, therefore created He
the soul and gave Himself in great love to her alone. Whereof art thou
made, O Soul, that thou soarest so high over all creatures and whilst
mingling in the Holy Trinity, yet remainest complete in thyself?
